cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a method for utilizing existing neural personalization techniques in the Federated Learning (FL) setting, which involves privacy-preserving and resource-efficient ways of learning user representations. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) due to the privacy-preserving aspect. The paper also involves techniques related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) due to the collaborative personalization and memory locality aspects.
